title: Ukraine Faces More Outages and Strikes Russian-Controlled Melitopol
description: The attack on Melitopol signals the importance of longer-range weapons in Ukraine’s campaign to recapture land in the south.

title: Biden’s Top Hostage Negotiator Details the Release of Brittney Griner
description: He said he told her “I’m here to take you home” when they met in Abu Dhabi for the prisoner exchange.

title: Indigenous Australians in Murujuga Fight to Preserve Heritage Sites
description: In Western Australia, new projects would supercharge gas drilling and processing. Traditional owners of the land say their heritage sites are threatened.

title: In Hostage Diplomacy, It’s Often the Hostage-Takers Who Pay
description: Detaining foreigners to wring concessions from their home country’s government holds perils for both sides, but especially, perhaps surprisingly, for the hostage takers.

title: 4 Charged With Corruption in Bribery Inquiry Linked to Qatar
description: The Belgian authorities announced other charges, including money laundering, in a case involving current and former members of the European Parliament.

title: Pants Recovered From Shipwreck Sell for $114,000 at Auction
description: The pants and other artifacts auctioned were salvaged from the S.S. Central America, a ship that sank in 1857.

title: Libyan Charged in 1988 Lockerbie Plane Bombing Is in FBI Custody
description: Abu Agila Mohammad Mas’ud, a Libyan bomb expert, is accused of building the explosive device used in the 1988 bombing of Pan Am Flight 103.

title: Ending a Civil War
description: A cease-fire in Ethiopia could bring an end to years of violence.

title: Prince Heinrich XIII and the Plot to Overthrow Germany’s Government
description: Prince Heinrich XIII was arrested this week as the suspected ringleader of a plan to overthrow the German government. Nostalgic for an imperial past, he embraced far-right conspiracy theories.

title: Former Prisoner in Iran Welcomes Brittney Griner to a ‘Bizarre Club’
description: Dr. Kylie Moore-Gilbert, who was in prison for two years, said she was unable to simply pick up where she left off, quitting her job, traveling and then writing about her experience.

title: For Moldova, War Next Door Brings Energy Crunch and Paid Protests
description: The tiny country, starved of natural gas and electricity because of the conflict in neighboring Ukraine, is confronting street rallies bankrolled by a pro-Russian politician to target its pro-Western government.
